_Lines and Surfaces_ is a `java` application that lets you see parametrized surfaces and curves in 3 dimensions.

These are *surfaces* given by a function $\mathbf{f}$:
$$ \mathbf{f}:(u,v)\in \mathbb{R^2} \rightarrow (f_1(u,v), f_2(u,v), f_3(u,v))^{T}$$
*Curves* given by a function $\boldsymbol{\gamma}$:

$$\boldsymbol{\gamma}:t\in\mathbb{R}\rightarrow(\gamma_1(t), \gamma_2(t), \gamma_3(t))^{T}$$

The `UI` accepts the usual syntax to define functions, it has the operators `+, -, *, /, ^`, and the functions `sin, cos, exp, tan, ln, ...`.After setting up your _curve_ or _surface_ you can generate a `.obj` file by pressing key `g`. 

Feel free to download the program below.

